tant advantages over traditional alternatives, namely
shorter extraction times, substantial savings of energy
and a reduced environmental hazard (less CO
ejected
in the atmosphere). The GC results showed that the
amount of oxygenated compounds and monoterpene
hydrocarbons increased and decreased, respectively by
MAHD method. Also, increasing 50% microwave in-
put power increased and decreased the concentration of
oxygenated compounds and monoterpene hydrocar-
bons. This result leads to the fact that the quality of
essential oil was increased by MAHD. So, MAHD can
be considered as a green technology. MAHD is a good
alternative for the extraction of essential oils from rose-
mary since it provides essential oils of similar quality
compared to conventional HD while reducing the time
and cost of the process drastically.
